This paper proposes a novel variant of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for multimodal image datasets. The paper focuses on improving the performance of GANs on unlabeled datasets without explicit clustering steps or objectives other than the adversary loss. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also introduces a learnable "analog-to-digital converter (ADC)" module, which maps a slice of the inputted multivariate Gaussian noise to discrete/digital noise (virtual label), enabling class-conditional sampling. This aspect of the paper aligns with the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper conducts experiments on several image datasets, demonstrating improved Frechet Inception Distance (FID), which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
